[assistant]   "summary": "Vert.x Web Client 5.0.1 is usable with its normal transitive dependencies and local HTTP servers, but its Vert.x Core/Netty 4.2.2 stack needs Java 25 native-image runtime properties for Unsafe access.",
[assistant]   "deterministic_setup": [],
[assistant]   "agent_guidance": "For native-image run coverage on JDK 25, configure the generated test project's nativeTest runtime arguments for io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 to include -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Meaningful tests can use an embedded Vert.x HttpServer bound to 127.0.0.1 with WebClient/WebClientOptions, BodyCodec JSON/string/buffer handling, forms/multipart upload, redirects, sessions/cookies, and caching; no external service is required.",
[assistant]   "risks": [
